== Overview ==

Chrono Trigger features over 200 enemies across different eras. This page documents enemy statistics and behaviors.

== Enemy Data Structure ==

Each enemy entry is 32 bytes:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $00-$01 || 2 || HP
|-
| $02-$03 || 2 || MP (unused for most)
|-
| $04 || 1 || Level
|-
| $05 || 1 || Power
|-
| $06 || 1 || Stamina
|-
| $07 || 1 || Speed
|-
| $08 || 1 || Magic
|-
| $09 || 1 || Magic Defense
|-
| $0A || 1 || Evade
|-
| $0B || 1 || Defense
|-
| $0C-$0D || 2 || Experience
|-
| $0E-$0F || 2 || Gold
|-
| $10 || 1 || Tech Points
|-
| $11 || 1 || Drop item ID
|-
| $12 || 1 || Drop rate
|-
| $13 || 1 || Charm item ID
|-
| $14-$1F || 12 || Attack patterns, resistances
|}

